  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "I created a path in a docker image in which to install the apps registry plugin, `/etc/helm/plugins/appr` with HELM_HOME set to /etc/helm in my Dockerfile, `env HELM_HOME=/etc/helm`. \r\n\r\nI install the plugin into that directory and can show that the plugin is installed.\r\n```\r\n# helm plugin list\r\nNAME    \tVERSION\tDESCRIPTION                              \r\nregistry\t0.5.0  \tThis plugin provides APPR client to Helm.\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut if I try to use that plugin, it errors:\r\n```\r\n# helm registry list quay.io\r\nError: unknown command \"registry\" for \"helm\"\r\nRun 'helm --help' for usage.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I symlink /etc/helm to ~/.helm, it works.\r\n\r\nPlease allow HELM_HOME to specify the home everywhere unless overridden by --home. The precedence I would expect to always work is:\r\n1. Unconfigured: use default (`$HOME/.helm`)\r\n2. HELM_HOME is set and no command line switch given: Use the setting in HELM_HOME.\r\n3. The command line switch --home is used, it should override HELM_HOME if it exists and should always be used.\r\n\r\n---\r\n```\r\n# helm version -c    \r\nClient: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.5.0\", GitCommit:\"012cb0ac1a1b2f888144ef5a67b8dab6c2d45be6\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n```",
